<p>Approximately <a href="https://bit.ly/1jMwYiz">4.5 months prior to a title's release</a>, preliminary cover/spread images should be distributed through the appropriate channels. The <em>image deltas</em> distribution group is setup for this purpose.</p>

<ol>

<li>
<p>Go to the <em>Distribution Groups</em> page by selecting <em>Groups</em> from the <em>Distribution</em> menu.</p>
<p><%= cdn_image "titleleaf-distribution-menu.png", alt: "Admin: Distribution Menu" %></p>
<p><%= cdn_image "titleleaf-distribution-groups-list.png", alt: "Admin: Distribution Groups List" %></p>
</li>

<li>
<p>Click the perform icon <%= titleleaf_perform_icon %> next to the <em>image deltas</em> group to create a new distribution template.</p>
</li>

<li>
<p>Set the options accordingly.</p>
<p>Set the options accordingly. For example, in the screenshot below, we are distributing images for the products identified by ISBN.</p>
<p><%= cdn_image "titleleaf-new-distribution-template-for-deltas-group.png", alt: "Admin: New distribution template for deltas group" %></p>
</li>

<li>
<p>Click the <em>Create</em> button. The <em>distribution template</em> that you created will result in multiple distributions. For more information, read about <a href="/guides/distributions/distribution-template">distribution templates</a>.</p>
</li>

</ol>
